post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,

As of today, August 29th, the OnCourse parent portal will display additional information including transportation and student schedules. Unlike PowerSchool, the OnCourse Connect portal does not require an app to view it – it is compatible with most browsers on smart phones and other mobile devices.

Note: You must submit the Annual Registration to access the OnCourse Connect parent portal. For more information regarding the Annual Registration, please visit our website, Latest News section, or use the link below.

http://www.springfieldschools.com/News/161#sthash.wq8G4zp5.dpbs

We look forward to having another great school year!

post_text:
This notice is to raise awareness of a dangerous “latest challenge” trend circulating through social media, specifically through the Tik Tok app.

The so-called “Skull Breaker Challenge” reportedly involves two individuals who deceive a third into jumping and falling forcefully backward. Serious injuries have been reported across the nation as a result.

Please talk to your child(ren) about this most recent challenge as well as many other dangerous trends shared on social media and the internet as we work together to keep our students safe.

Below is an article with additional details.

https://www.insideedition.com/tiktok-skull-breaker-challenge-can-lead-to-broken-bones-and-criminal-charges-police-and-parents

Thank you

post_text: Congratulations to Jonathan Dayton’s boys cross country team who won the Union County Conference Championships in the Valley division for the second year in a row! Daniel Galao-Birkmann ran a time of 17:31, Colin Riley 18:29, Harrison Turner 19:16, Ian McLeer 19:23, and Luke Hernandez 19:24, earning them first team all conference. The girls team placed fourth overall in the Mountain division. Abbey Hochreiner ran a time of 19:57 and Catriona Corbett 20:15 earning them first team all conference. Go Bulldogs!
